Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers
TOKYO , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Japanese newspapers Monday .
Asahi , Yomiuri , Mainichi , Nihon Keizai :
-- Japan and the United States agreed on Sunday to launch joint research on a theater missile defense ( TMD ) system for Japan beginning in fiscal 1999 .
Yomiuri :
-- The Japanese Trade Union Confederation ( Rengo ) has decided not to set a unified wage hike target for next spring 's collective bargaining as member unions are more interested in measures to ensure and protect employment rather than obtain large pay increases .
Yomiuri , Mainichi :
-- Malaysia 's ousted former Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim was detained by the police Sunday night , a few hours after he staged a rally in the capital calling for Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad to step down immediately .
Nihon Keizai :
-- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi plans to declare Japan-U.S. cooperation in restructuring the international financial system .
